President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Puerto Rico and ordered federal assistance to help with the aftermath of Hurricane Maria. The Department of Homeland Security's Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) will coordinate all disaster relief efforts. This declaration will provide resources and funding for debris removal, emergency protective measures, and other necessary assistance. Alejandro DeLaCampa has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.